sub_title: Country Operations Manager at APAVE - GUYANA
summary:
Operations Manager overseeing activities at every level of the organization onshore and offshore. 
Involvement into day to day activities with the technical teams and other departments. Development of strategic plans to ensure everyone completes their tasks on schedule and safely. 

IRATA Level 3 Rope Access Supervisor and Manager  Involves fully briefing assistants and all involved on safe systems of work and duties to be completed.
Able to identify areas of strength and weakness of workforce and implement strategies to improve standard of operations. Able to control cost on all levels uncompromising quality.
Working on IRATA audits, training and equipment assessments.
Part of Offshore projects like:
Hull Integrity Inspections Supervisor, working on corrosion prevention and structural analyses of the FPSO units and Fixed Platforms.
Mooring Chain Inspections and replacement.
